WEBVTT

00:02.120 --> 00:05.120
[ Sleeping At Last's "One"
plays ]

00:05.120 --> 00:07.120
♪♪

00:07.120 --> 00:08.920
Meredith:
Time is a strange thing.

00:08.920 --> 00:11.790
♪ Hold on for a minute ♪

00:11.790 --> 00:14.420
When you're waiting for
something good to happen,

00:14.420 --> 00:16.670
it can feel like time
is dragging on.

00:16.670 --> 00:18.540
♪ Over time ♪

00:18.540 --> 00:21.120
But when you want it
to slow down,

00:21.120 --> 00:24.540
it goes by
in the blink of an eye.

00:24.540 --> 00:27.880
♪ Now hold on, let me finish ♪

00:27.880 --> 00:32.460
♪ Perfect exists in this life ♪

00:32.460 --> 00:36.330
The odd part is
time isn't real.

00:36.330 --> 00:38.250
♪ If we try ♪

00:39.790 --> 00:43.040
♪ I, I-I, I-I ♪

00:43.040 --> 00:46.080
It's a concept imagined
by scientists

00:46.080 --> 00:49.540
based on the imperfect movement
of the earth around the sun.

00:49.540 --> 00:56.120
♪ I'll write an anthem
worth repeating ♪

00:56.120 --> 00:58.500
So why do we put
so much importance

00:58.500 --> 01:00.380
on something that's
just a theory?

01:00.380 --> 01:03.380
♪ I wanna feel
the transformation ♪

01:07.210 --> 01:11.120
♪ A melody of reformation ♪

01:11.120 --> 01:13.460
Because it's all we have.

01:13.460 --> 01:16.170
♪♪

01:16.170 --> 01:17.580
Hey, do you two
want to come over

01:17.580 --> 01:19.080
tomorrow morning
for presents?

01:19.080 --> 01:21.420
You know, Owen and I are trying
to establish our own traditions

01:21.420 --> 01:23.460
with Leo, just give him
a little bit of normalcy

01:23.460 --> 01:24.920
while we still can.
Right.

01:24.920 --> 01:27.170
Before his mother/sister
comes home from rehab?

01:27.170 --> 01:29.710
And his half-sibling
arrives, yeah.

01:29.710 --> 01:32.420
Well, kids can make anything
normal, so he'll be fine.

01:32.420 --> 01:33.420
Thanks.

01:33.420 --> 01:35.000
Dr. Grey?

01:35.000 --> 01:37.620
Uh, I start my ICU rotation
tomorrow,

01:37.620 --> 01:41.250
and I was wondering if you
have any advice on...that.

01:42.420 --> 01:44.500
Well, first of all, Schmitt,
don't call them "that."

01:44.500 --> 01:47.710
Sorry, I just mean,
it's so...emotional in there.

01:47.710 --> 01:50.250
Well, it's the ICU,
and she's been here for a month.

01:50.250 --> 01:51.830
She's off
the sedatives now.

01:51.830 --> 01:53.330
We don't know
when she'll wake up

01:53.330 --> 01:55.170
or even if
she'll wake up.

01:55.170 --> 01:57.620
You know, it's brutal,
and it's depressing.

01:57.620 --> 02:00.670
And it can make you feel like
you're going insane.

02:00.670 --> 02:01.580
Right.

02:01.580 --> 02:03.540
So, I --

02:03.540 --> 02:07.580
You are going to watch
Natasha very closely.

02:07.580 --> 02:09.540
You will examine her
every day.

02:09.540 --> 02:11.880
If there's any change,
any type of change,

02:11.880 --> 02:13.670
you'll page me immediately.

02:13.670 --> 02:14.960
Okay?
Okay.

02:17.330 --> 02:19.290
And you should go outside
on your breaks,

02:19.290 --> 02:20.670
because you can feel
like you're losing

02:20.670 --> 02:22.210
all sense
of time in here.

02:23.620 --> 02:25.420
[ Telephone rings in distance ]

02:25.420 --> 02:26.920
[ Sighs ]

02:26.920 --> 02:28.460
You had the husband?
Yeah.

02:28.460 --> 02:30.330
Ice skate to the tibia.
You?

02:30.330 --> 02:32.540
Ouch. Wife had
a hell of a concussion.

02:32.540 --> 02:34.000
Most wonderful time
of the year, right?

02:35.380 --> 02:37.420
Hey.

02:37.420 --> 02:38.790
It's snowing.

02:38.790 --> 02:44.750
♪♪

02:44.750 --> 02:46.500
What are you guys
doing for Christmas?

02:46.500 --> 02:50.750
Oh, you know, Leo's too young
to absorb any of it.

02:50.750 --> 02:52.920
I think we're gonna do
presents and cocoa

02:52.920 --> 02:54.210
and cinnamon buns,
all that.

02:54.210 --> 02:55.580
Hopefully some
of it'll stick.

02:55.580 --> 02:56.830
Yeah, that's sweet.

02:56.830 --> 02:59.790
And Amelia has to go to rehab
to visit Betty. Yeah.

02:59.790 --> 03:01.120
Right.
The usual.

03:01.120 --> 03:02.000
Yeah.

03:05.170 --> 03:08.290
So, we're gonna, um...

03:08.290 --> 03:10.170
We're having Christmas dinner
tomorrow night,

03:10.170 --> 03:13.830
and Amelia wanted me
to invite you.

03:13.830 --> 03:16.620
Oh, no, no.
Thanks. No.

03:16.620 --> 03:18.380
I'm -- I'm covering for you
in the pit, remember?

03:18.380 --> 03:19.830
Oh, right, right.
Yeah.

03:19.830 --> 03:20.960
Of course.
And thank you, again.

03:20.960 --> 03:22.790
Yeah, of course.

03:22.790 --> 03:32.330
♪♪

03:32.330 --> 03:36.040
We're gonna find
our own traditions, too.

03:36.040 --> 03:37.330
I know.

03:40.080 --> 03:42.500
Merry Christmas, Owen.

03:42.500 --> 03:52.120
♪♪

03:52.120 --> 03:53.210
[ Telephone rings ]

03:53.210 --> 03:54.500
It's a unique choice.

03:54.500 --> 03:56.250
I mean, I don't think
we've ever had a chief

03:56.250 --> 03:58.210
give us cured meat before.

03:58.210 --> 04:00.250
I did something nice,
and you're mocking me for it.

04:00.250 --> 04:01.380
Oh, wait!
Did you tell her?

04:01.380 --> 04:02.620
We're having
a New Year's Eve party.

04:02.620 --> 04:04.710
Attending and fellows only.
Champagne.

04:04.710 --> 04:06.710
Little snacky things
on crackers.

04:06.710 --> 04:08.290
Very classy.
How glamorous.

04:08.290 --> 04:10.290
I know.
You should invite Link.

04:10.290 --> 04:11.540
I mean,
I already invited him,

04:11.540 --> 04:13.250
but y-you should ask him
to be your date,

04:13.250 --> 04:14.500
'cause I already told him
that you would.

04:14.500 --> 04:15.500
Jo --

04:15.500 --> 04:16.670
Ooh, sorry.
Ohh! Oh, my --

04:16.670 --> 04:18.920
Oh.
Hey.

04:18.920 --> 04:21.420
Hi.
Um, I-I was just leaving,

04:21.420 --> 04:22.710
and it looks like
you are, too.

04:22.710 --> 04:24.710
Do you want to take
our hams out for a drink?

04:24.710 --> 04:26.460
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, that sounds amazing,

04:26.460 --> 04:28.830
but I have to get home
because it's Christmas Eve.

04:28.830 --> 04:30.580
I have to put the kids to bed
so Santa can come.

04:30.580 --> 04:31.620
Right.
Yeah.

04:31.620 --> 04:33.460
Soon though?
Yes. Yeah.

04:34.620 --> 04:36.620
Oh, you know, actually,
the Karevs are having

04:36.620 --> 04:39.210
a very classy
New Year's Eve party.

04:39.210 --> 04:40.670
I'll be there.
Okay.

04:40.670 --> 04:42.250
No --
Dark blue scrubs only.

04:42.250 --> 04:43.830
She can have a plus one.

04:43.830 --> 04:45.880
You're supposed
to read my tone.
Read your what?

04:45.880 --> 04:47.580
Jo, I'm a big girl.

04:47.580 --> 04:49.500
I can handle
my own love life.

04:49.500 --> 04:50.880
-Thanks for the ham, Chief.
-You're welcome.

04:50.880 --> 04:52.920
Here comes Santa Claus.

04:52.920 --> 04:54.540
[ Laughs ]
Link: This is for you.

04:54.540 --> 04:56.880
Cookies for Santa, in case you
don't feel like baking later.

04:56.880 --> 04:58.790
Link is spending
his Christmas Eve

04:58.790 --> 05:00.500
visiting kids
in the cancer ward.

05:01.710 --> 05:02.710
Seriously?

05:02.710 --> 05:03.750
Seriously.

05:03.750 --> 05:05.290
Seriously.

05:05.290 --> 05:07.290
You're mocking him
for doing something even nicer.

05:07.290 --> 05:08.380
You should take
a look at that.

05:08.380 --> 05:10.080
We'll see you
New Year's Eve.

05:10.080 --> 05:11.880
Meredith: Bye, Santa.

05:11.880 --> 05:13.880
You are in
a love triangle.

05:13.880 --> 05:15.790
There's no love.
There's no triangle.

05:15.790 --> 05:17.120
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

05:17.120 --> 05:18.670
Unless, of course,

05:18.670 --> 05:20.620
the ham, the cookies, and I
are a triangle.

05:20.620 --> 05:21.620
[ Laughs ]

05:21.620 --> 05:23.120
She's totally
in a love triangle.

05:23.120 --> 05:24.580
Mm-hmm.

05:24.580 --> 05:26.330
[ Knock on door ]

05:26.330 --> 05:27.920
[ Sighs ]

05:28.790 --> 05:30.040
Hey.
Hey.

05:30.040 --> 05:31.120
Uh, sorry
I didn't call first.

05:31.120 --> 05:32.830
Oh, it's okay.
Come in.

05:32.830 --> 05:34.290
Uh, I can't stay.

05:34.290 --> 05:36.250
Just, uh -- just wanted
to drop these off for Tuck

05:36.250 --> 05:38.380
for in the morning
from me.

05:38.380 --> 05:40.500
Oh.
Thank you.

05:40.500 --> 05:43.000
Uh -- Uh, but I put your name
on all the gifts I got him.

05:43.000 --> 05:44.210
Why would you do that?

05:44.210 --> 05:45.710
Well, 'cause
they're from us.

05:45.710 --> 05:47.080
It's funny.

05:47.080 --> 05:49.290
I-I don't remember us
going shopping together.

05:49.290 --> 05:51.460
I just didn't want him
to think that --

05:51.460 --> 05:53.500
You called a time-out
on our marriage?

05:53.500 --> 05:55.330
Okay.
I'm sorry.

05:55.330 --> 05:57.380
Uh, thank you
for the gifts.

05:57.380 --> 06:00.040
I'll make sure
that he opens them.

06:00.040 --> 06:03.540
Uh, what are you -- Wait.
Where are you gonna be tomorrow?

06:03.540 --> 06:05.540
On call. You know,
Christmas is a big day for us.

06:05.540 --> 06:06.620
Oh, us, too.

06:06.620 --> 06:08.170
Uh, maybe I'll see you
in the pit.

06:08.170 --> 06:09.880
Maybe don't sound so hopeful
that somebody gets injured

06:09.880 --> 06:11.750
in a fire on Christmas.

06:11.750 --> 06:14.040
Right.

06:14.040 --> 06:17.170
[ "We Wish You
a Merry Christmas" plays ]

06:17.170 --> 06:19.710
♪♪

06:19.710 --> 06:21.080
[ Utensils clack ]

06:21.080 --> 06:23.750
Anybody want
to play cards?

06:23.750 --> 06:25.170
I play a mean Gin Rummy.

06:25.170 --> 06:27.250
Oh, you don't want to do that
unless you want to lose.

06:27.250 --> 06:29.540
I am the master of Gin Rummy
in this house.
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

06:29.540 --> 06:32.380
I'm sorry, kids.
I'm just exhausted.

06:32.380 --> 06:35.210
Would I be a party pooper
if I just went to bed?

06:35.210 --> 06:37.000
Of course, Mom.
Get your rest.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.210
Okay.
I'm sorry.

06:39.210 --> 06:42.710
Couldn't even chase Harriet
around that tree this morning.

06:42.710 --> 06:46.040
Thank you so much for taking
care of Christmas dinner.

06:46.040 --> 06:48.250
I've just been no help at all.

06:48.250 --> 06:50.540
We have Christmas dinner
catered every year, Mom.

06:50.540 --> 06:51.880
There's no reason
to change that.

06:51.880 --> 06:54.000
[ Chuckles ]
Merry Christmas, baby.
Okay.

06:54.000 --> 06:55.420
Maggie.
Merry Christmas.

06:55.420 --> 06:56.670
Can I help you
upstairs?

06:56.670 --> 06:58.420
Oh, no, no.

06:58.420 --> 07:02.290
No, I can make it
to my bed on my own.

07:06.170 --> 07:07.420
[ Sighs ]

07:07.420 --> 07:10.380
She doesn't let me
help her do anything.

07:10.380 --> 07:12.500
She'll get there.

07:12.500 --> 07:13.790
I hope so.

07:13.790 --> 07:16.790
♪♪

07:19.080 --> 07:22.290
It was fine.
A little boring.

07:22.290 --> 07:24.000
I kinda wished
you were there.

07:24.000 --> 07:25.710
At Christmas?

07:25.710 --> 07:27.290
With your family?

07:27.290 --> 07:29.210
Yeah.
Why? Is that weird?

07:29.210 --> 07:31.170
No.

07:31.170 --> 07:33.750
I'll come next year, and I'll
bring some Chanukkah gelt.

07:33.750 --> 07:35.790
[ Chuckles ]

07:37.460 --> 07:39.330
It's creepy in here.

07:39.330 --> 07:41.080
I'll protect you.

07:41.080 --> 07:42.500
You are so cheesy.

07:42.500 --> 07:44.460
[ Laughs ]

07:44.460 --> 07:46.460
Hey, uh, Dr. Shepherd asked me
to come check on Natasha.

07:46.460 --> 07:48.040
Man: Help!
Can you --

07:48.040 --> 07:49.210
Hello!
Somebody?

07:49.210 --> 07:50.420
Page Dr. Grey.

07:52.000 --> 07:53.620
Oh, my God, it's Natasha.
She's...

07:55.500 --> 07:58.000
She's awake.

07:58.000 --> 07:59.960
[ Laughs ]

07:59.960 --> 08:02.960
♪♪

08:15.540 --> 08:18.000
Garrett: [ Clears throat ]
Thank you.

08:18.000 --> 08:20.540
Thank you, thank you,
thank you.

08:20.540 --> 08:22.620
I'm saying it a lot
for the both of us.

08:22.620 --> 08:23.620
Meredith: Schmitt?

08:23.620 --> 08:27.540
Natasha Deon, 45,
hospital day 35.

08:27.540 --> 08:29.540
Neuro -- She regained
consciousness overnight.

08:29.540 --> 08:31.420
She is now A&O times three.

08:31.420 --> 08:33.170
Cardio and pulmonary --
She's on a vent

08:33.170 --> 08:35.920
and has an open thoracostomy
for empyema drainage.

08:35.920 --> 08:38.210
MSK -- Spine was cleared,

08:38.210 --> 08:40.380
and her pelvis was fixed
internally.

08:40.380 --> 08:41.750
When will she
be able to talk?

08:41.750 --> 08:44.000
We're working on decreasing
her vent settings first.

08:44.000 --> 08:45.380
Meredith: We also have
to get her nutrition up.

08:45.380 --> 08:47.830
She's weak and has been
through quite a lot.

08:47.830 --> 08:49.330
Maggie:
We can close the thoracostomy
today, though,

08:49.330 --> 08:51.040
since her lungs
are doing so much better.

08:51.040 --> 08:52.750
Natasha, we need you
to get strong for us.

08:52.750 --> 08:55.120
I'm gonna get you up and out
of that bed soon, okay?

08:55.120 --> 08:56.880
Meredith: Let's make sure
the respiratory therapist

08:56.880 --> 08:58.290
brings that peep down to 5.

08:58.290 --> 09:00.460
Welcome back, Natasha.

09:00.460 --> 09:02.580
You may get
that planetarium wedding yet.

09:02.580 --> 09:03.960
At this point,
I'd settle for a courthouse.

09:03.960 --> 09:05.790
[ Chuckles ]

09:05.790 --> 09:07.380
Nice work, Grey.

09:10.960 --> 09:13.380
[ Chuckles ]
Love triangle.

09:13.380 --> 09:15.250
When are you gonna stop
stringing him along, huh?

09:16.540 --> 09:18.000
Excuse me?

09:18.000 --> 09:19.790
You heard me.

09:19.790 --> 09:21.830
Link -- he likes you, and you
keep giving him false hope.

09:21.830 --> 09:23.330
Who says it's false?

09:23.330 --> 09:25.460
Oh, please.
We both know it is.

09:25.460 --> 09:26.830
Do we?

09:26.830 --> 09:30.250
[ Speaking Italian ]

09:30.250 --> 09:32.830
Andrew.

09:32.830 --> 09:34.120
New Year's Eve.

09:34.120 --> 09:35.380
Is that a date?

09:35.380 --> 09:37.120
Or is that like,
"Oh, come to this party,

09:37.120 --> 09:38.920
and we'll make eyes
at each other over the punch,

09:38.920 --> 09:40.710
but I'm not really brave enough
to talk to you in public"?

09:40.710 --> 09:42.250
I've been called
a lot of things.

09:42.250 --> 09:44.540
"Not brave enough"
isn't one of them.

09:46.580 --> 09:49.620
Fine.
It's a date.

09:49.620 --> 09:51.120
Woman over PA:
Dr. Brooks, dial Admitting.

09:51.120 --> 09:54.670
Dr. Brooks, dial Admitting.

09:54.670 --> 09:56.710
You look good.

09:56.710 --> 09:59.120
Your hair,
it's shinier.

09:59.120 --> 10:01.750
Oh, ew. Please don't
talk about my hair.

10:01.750 --> 10:03.880
Okay.

10:03.880 --> 10:06.920
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:06.920 --> 10:09.420
How's Leo?
He's good.

10:09.420 --> 10:13.210
Yeah, he's teething like crazy,
but he's good.

10:13.210 --> 10:14.670
You miss him?

10:14.670 --> 10:16.080
I mean,

10:16.080 --> 10:19.790
not as much as I miss drugs,
but yeah, a bit.

10:19.790 --> 10:21.580
Well, that's good.

10:21.580 --> 10:22.920
Identifying that.

10:22.920 --> 10:24.830
It's...part
of the process.

10:24.830 --> 10:27.540
No, it's not part
of the process.

10:27.540 --> 10:29.420
I just miss drugs.

10:29.420 --> 10:31.290
I know they ruined
my life,

10:31.290 --> 10:34.170
but they made me feel
better than anything.

10:34.170 --> 10:35.710
Better than being a mom.

10:35.710 --> 10:37.380
Oh, God.

10:37.380 --> 10:39.790
That's so stupid.
I shouldn't even be a mom.

10:39.790 --> 10:41.210
I'm a kid.

10:42.670 --> 10:44.080
I should just
give you guys Leo

10:44.080 --> 10:46.620
and pretend none
of this ever happened.

10:46.620 --> 10:48.210
Betty...

10:48.210 --> 10:54.250
♪♪

10:54.250 --> 10:55.710
It's New Year's Eve.

10:57.330 --> 10:59.040
Don't you have
somewhere to be?

10:59.040 --> 11:03.380
♪♪

11:04.620 --> 11:06.330
[ Alexi Von Guggenberg's
"Stand Out" plays ]

11:06.330 --> 11:08.330
[ Indistinct conversations ]

11:08.330 --> 11:14.960
♪♪

11:14.960 --> 11:17.040
Woman: Girl, look at you!
[ Laughs ]

11:17.040 --> 11:19.000
♪ Can't help but stand out ♪

11:19.000 --> 11:21.330
♪ Ooh, can't help myself ♪

11:21.330 --> 11:22.790
♪ I can't help but stand out ♪

11:22.790 --> 11:26.120
Oh, hey, um, weren't you
supposed to be covering the ICU?

11:26.120 --> 11:27.580
Oh, uh,
Natasha was using

11:27.580 --> 11:29.250
the speaking valve
for the first time,

11:29.250 --> 11:31.040
so Dr. Grey said
she wanted to stay.

11:31.040 --> 11:32.380
♪ Ooh, can't help myself ♪

11:32.380 --> 11:33.710
♪ Can't help but stand out ♪

11:33.710 --> 11:35.830
Hey. Where are you
right now?

11:35.830 --> 11:37.080
♪ No limitations ♪

11:37.080 --> 11:39.080
Sorry, I'm just...
distracted.

11:39.080 --> 11:40.750
♪ Tell me the rules
so I can break them ♪

11:40.750 --> 11:42.080
Let's get out of here.

11:42.080 --> 11:43.330
♪ I keep slippin' in
their conversations ♪

11:43.330 --> 11:44.920
The ball hasn't
even dropped yet.

11:44.920 --> 11:46.250
The ball can drop
in our bed.

11:46.250 --> 11:47.830
Hmm?

11:47.830 --> 11:49.540
I did not mean that
to sound so graphic.

11:49.540 --> 11:50.960
[ Both laugh ]

11:50.960 --> 11:52.380
♪ I ain't doing my job ♪

11:52.380 --> 11:54.580
Miranda: Do you think
I can ask him over

11:54.580 --> 11:58.170
after his shift,
like, for a toast maybe?

11:58.170 --> 12:01.880
Uh, I mean, my son's with his
father, so I don't know --

12:01.880 --> 12:04.210
Oh, would Ben think
that's a booty call?

12:04.210 --> 12:05.420
He might think
that's a booty call.

12:05.420 --> 12:07.500
Well, maybe that's not
such a bad thing.

12:07.500 --> 12:10.120
Okay, hey, everyone!
It's almost midnight!

12:10.120 --> 12:11.500
Alex: Come on.
Hurry, hurry.

12:11.500 --> 12:14.620
[ Bottles clinking ]

12:14.620 --> 12:16.880
-Oh, no, I'll take one.
-Thank you.

12:16.880 --> 12:19.380
Oh, you look...like I should've
joined the Army.

12:19.380 --> 12:20.620
[ Both chuckle ]

12:20.620 --> 12:24.290
All: 10, 9, 8,

12:24.290 --> 12:27.710
7, 6, 5,

12:27.710 --> 12:32.080
4, 3, 2, 1...

12:32.080 --> 12:34.120
Happy New Year!

12:34.120 --> 12:35.830
[ Cheers and laughter ]

12:35.830 --> 12:37.540
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

12:37.540 --> 12:39.790
Happy New Year.

12:39.790 --> 12:42.380
[ Chuckles ]

12:42.380 --> 12:44.710
Happy New Year.

12:44.710 --> 12:46.330
Shut up.

12:47.960 --> 12:49.790
Happy New Year, Dr. Karev.

12:49.790 --> 12:52.080
Happy New Year, Dr. Karev.

12:52.080 --> 12:54.080
♪ Cuz I'm gonna live
my life free ♪

12:54.080 --> 12:56.120
♪ Can't help but stand out ♪

12:56.120 --> 12:58.540
And may this year be
everything you wish for.

12:58.540 --> 12:59.620
We want to thank you all for...

12:59.620 --> 13:01.210
How are you feeling
off the vent?

13:01.210 --> 13:02.960
...and whether all your dreams
came true this year,

13:02.960 --> 13:04.380
or you simply...

13:04.380 --> 13:05.670
[ Weakly ] Like I haven't
breathed on my own

13:05.670 --> 13:08.000
in two months.

13:08.000 --> 13:09.080
Then you're doing well.

13:12.460 --> 13:14.790
Garrett went to find us
sparkling water

13:14.790 --> 13:17.290
so we could pretend
it's champagne.

13:17.290 --> 13:19.120
He's a good one, huh?
He is.

13:19.120 --> 13:21.000
He was by your side
the entire time.

13:22.460 --> 13:24.210
I could hear him.

13:24.210 --> 13:29.380
He talked to me all day about
you and the other doctors.

13:29.380 --> 13:32.290
Shouldn't you be kissing
one of them right now?

13:32.290 --> 13:33.500
Kissing who?

13:33.500 --> 13:36.330
One of the doctors
who likes you.

13:36.330 --> 13:40.040
Garrett calls them
Abercrombie and Stitch.

13:40.040 --> 13:42.040
[ Both laugh ]

13:42.040 --> 13:43.380
Yeah!
Come over here!

13:43.380 --> 13:45.670
Oh, dang!
We missed it.

13:45.670 --> 13:47.040
Happy New Year, guys.

13:47.040 --> 13:49.830
[ Keys clack ]

13:49.830 --> 13:53.500
TV announcer: 10...
10, 9, 8...

13:53.500 --> 13:56.500
Kiss the one who
turns back time for you.

13:56.500 --> 14:01.830
...5, 4, 3, 2, 1...

14:01.830 --> 14:03.120
Happy New Year!

14:03.120 --> 14:05.000
Happy New Year!

14:05.000 --> 14:06.920
Happy New Year.

14:06.920 --> 14:08.330
Oh!

14:08.330 --> 14:15.290
♪♪

14:15.290 --> 14:17.000
♪ All right, ohh ♪

14:17.000 --> 14:18.790
Scotch, neat.

14:18.790 --> 14:20.170
Hey, how you doing?

14:20.170 --> 14:24.000
Good, good.

14:24.000 --> 14:26.880
You, uh, been
playing lately?

14:26.880 --> 14:28.920
No.
Been busy.

14:28.920 --> 14:30.620
Same.

14:30.620 --> 14:31.960
♪ Ain't got no regrets ♪

14:31.960 --> 14:33.120
♪ Ain't got no regrets ♪

14:33.120 --> 14:35.290
She stand you up, too?

14:35.290 --> 14:36.460
Looks like it.

14:36.460 --> 14:38.080
♪ Till there ain't nothing
left ♪

14:38.080 --> 14:41.290
♪ Feels like my heart will beat
right out of my chest ♪

14:41.290 --> 14:42.080
♪ This is as good as it gets ♪

14:47.330 --> 14:50.040
Natasha Deon, 45,
hospital day 45.

14:50.040 --> 14:51.920
Neuro and cardio unchanged.

14:51.920 --> 14:54.790
Pulmonary -- She has tolerated
her speaking valve trials

14:54.790 --> 14:56.330
with intermittent oxygen.

14:56.330 --> 14:58.380
We will remove
the chest tube today.

14:58.380 --> 15:00.380
GI -- She's on tube feeds.

15:00.380 --> 15:03.420
PT/OT --
She made it bed to chair.

15:03.420 --> 15:06.750
Well, there has been
a lot of progress.

15:06.750 --> 15:08.420
We're still not out
of the woods yet,

15:08.420 --> 15:11.750
but, um, do you have any
questions for us?

15:11.750 --> 15:14.120
When do I get to eat?
Jo: [ Laughs ]

15:14.120 --> 15:16.080
She's been awake for 11 days,
and she's been asking

15:16.080 --> 15:18.290
about tacos for 10 of them.

15:18.290 --> 15:20.540
Tacos are a ways away,
I'm afraid.

15:20.540 --> 15:22.580
But we can --
we can do Jell-O.

15:22.580 --> 15:24.580
The speech and swallow therapist
will try that today.

15:24.580 --> 15:25.750
I'll take it.

15:25.750 --> 15:27.830
Uh, watermelon.

15:27.830 --> 15:29.170
Okay, you take care.

15:31.830 --> 15:33.380
Hey.
Dr. Grey.

15:33.380 --> 15:34.460
I haven't seen you
in a few days.

15:34.460 --> 15:36.040
How have you been?
Stood up.

15:36.040 --> 15:38.500
Sorry.
I don't know if you've
ever been stood up before,

15:38.500 --> 15:39.670
but it feels pretty awful.

15:39.670 --> 15:42.500
Well, I had a patient.
You have a phone.

15:42.500 --> 15:44.170
Woman over PA:
Dr. Rainey to Peds ICU.

15:44.170 --> 15:46.670
Dr. Rainey to Peds ICU.
[ Sighs ]

15:46.670 --> 15:47.790
Look, it's been fun.

15:47.790 --> 15:49.380
The waiting.
The build up. The game.

15:49.380 --> 15:50.880
But that?
That wasn't fun.

15:50.880 --> 15:52.330
That was just rude.
You're right.

15:52.330 --> 15:54.710
I'm a good guy,
Meredith.

15:54.710 --> 15:56.040
But I'm not a doormat.
[ Elevator bell dings ]

15:56.040 --> 15:57.290
And if that's what you're after,
then I don't know.

15:57.290 --> 15:58.830
Maybe Link is your guy
after all.

16:05.000 --> 16:06.380
A little more.
A little more!

16:06.380 --> 16:08.330
Good!
There you go!

16:08.330 --> 16:10.380
Please don't talk to me
like I'm a child.

16:10.380 --> 16:12.250
It's perfectly normal
to feel --

16:12.250 --> 16:13.880
How do you know
what "normal" is?

16:13.880 --> 16:16.170
Have you ever had
your spine carved open

16:16.170 --> 16:17.420
and dug around in?
[ Sighs ]

16:17.420 --> 16:18.670
Huh?

16:18.670 --> 16:22.040
Um...Marsha,

16:22.040 --> 16:24.000
can you give us a minute,
please?

16:24.000 --> 16:25.250
Yeah.
Thank you.

16:26.830 --> 16:28.460
[ Sighs ]

16:28.460 --> 16:30.920
Richard, spare me the lecture
about recovery.

16:30.920 --> 16:32.460
I know that's
the pain talking.

16:32.460 --> 16:35.250
No, that is me talking,
and I say she's a pain.

16:35.250 --> 16:37.380
You're a pain
in my entire ass!

16:37.380 --> 16:38.460
[ Sighs ]

16:38.460 --> 16:39.960
I asked her to give me
some exercises

16:39.960 --> 16:43.500
so that I could get back
to my sensual self,

16:43.500 --> 16:45.000
and she said [High-pitched]
"Don't worry

16:45.000 --> 16:46.420
your little heart
about that"

16:46.420 --> 16:48.580
[Normal voice] like
I'm some dried-up old mop.

16:48.580 --> 16:50.040
Well, I'm sure that's
not what she meant.

16:50.040 --> 16:51.880
Then what did she mean?

16:51.880 --> 16:53.500
It's not like
these pain meds

16:53.500 --> 16:55.710
are letting me have any
sexual appetite anyway.

16:55.710 --> 16:57.000
The average
recovery time --

16:57.000 --> 16:58.500
Since when am I average?

16:58.500 --> 16:59.710
[ Speaks indistinctly ]
Don't talk to me about time.

16:59.710 --> 17:01.620
Don't help me.

17:01.620 --> 17:03.290
[ Sighs ]

17:03.290 --> 17:08.330
♪♪

17:08.330 --> 17:10.170
Hey, sorry I'm late.
You already started.

17:10.170 --> 17:12.750
This gel is really cold, and I
have to get back to the pit.

17:12.750 --> 17:14.460
You said we were gonna
do these things together.

17:14.460 --> 17:15.880
You can't just --
What do you want me to do?

17:15.880 --> 17:17.710
Every time I have to
be a parent, wait for you?

17:17.710 --> 17:19.380
Yeah, but if you say
you're gonna wait,
then you can't just --

17:19.380 --> 17:21.290
This baby is gonna be outside
of my body eventually.

17:21.290 --> 17:23.000
Oh, really?
Is that how it works?

17:23.000 --> 17:24.080
Please explain it to me,
Teddy.

17:24.080 --> 17:25.500
[ Heartbeat ]

17:25.500 --> 17:26.920
Oh, my God.

17:28.460 --> 17:31.120
It's a --
Oh, wow.

17:34.380 --> 17:37.000
We're having a baby girl.

17:37.000 --> 17:44.750
♪♪

17:44.750 --> 17:46.830
[ Siren wails ]

17:46.830 --> 17:48.580
Hey! Ben!

17:48.580 --> 17:50.540
Hey.
Hey.

17:50.540 --> 17:51.750
MVC out on Elliott.

17:51.750 --> 17:53.540
This -- This black ice
is no joke.

17:53.540 --> 17:55.750
Did you put
your snow tires on?
Uh, I will.

17:55.750 --> 17:59.380
Ben, um, I need to
tell you something --

17:59.380 --> 18:00.920
or ask you something.

18:00.920 --> 18:03.830
I don't have the words ready,
but my heart is.

18:05.620 --> 18:08.420
I want you to come home,
Ben.

18:08.420 --> 18:09.750
Please.

18:13.500 --> 18:17.790
I mean -- it's lonely at
the house when Tuck is gone,

18:17.790 --> 18:19.460
and, uh, the fence,
uh, it --

18:19.460 --> 18:21.290
it blew down after
the windstorm.

18:21.290 --> 18:22.750
I haven't had a chance --
No.

18:22.750 --> 18:24.500
Come home, Ben.

18:24.500 --> 18:25.920
Please.

18:25.920 --> 18:27.120
Come home.

18:30.580 --> 18:32.620
Miranda, I --

18:32.620 --> 18:34.120
I love you.

18:36.710 --> 18:38.120
But you broke my heart.

18:39.620 --> 18:42.170
I'm not coming home just because
now you're lonely

18:42.170 --> 18:44.500
and the fence
needs patching.

18:44.500 --> 18:45.830
Okay.

18:45.830 --> 18:48.540
O-Okay, no, uh,
that's not what I meant.

18:48.540 --> 18:49.960
Uh...

18:49.960 --> 18:51.540
You know I haven't
been myself.

18:51.540 --> 18:53.040
It was my meds.

18:53.040 --> 18:57.000
I was working on
my physical health so much

18:57.000 --> 18:59.000
that I was ignoring
my mental --

18:59.000 --> 19:01.620
My anxieties, again,
they --

19:04.210 --> 19:08.670
I-It wasn't the job,
and it was not your fault.

19:08.670 --> 19:10.960
But I'm --
I'm handling it.

19:10.960 --> 19:12.920
I'm -- I'm being treated.

19:12.920 --> 19:15.330
I'm better now.

19:15.330 --> 19:17.330
Dispatcher: Structure fire
at Mercer and Fairview.

19:17.330 --> 19:18.880
All nearby units, respond.
[ Static crackles ]

19:18.880 --> 19:20.250
W-We have to go.

19:20.250 --> 19:21.670
I'll talk to you later.

19:21.670 --> 19:22.710
Ben?

19:24.540 --> 19:26.000
[ Engine starts ]

19:26.000 --> 19:27.250
I'm sorry.

19:27.250 --> 19:29.040
[ Siren wails ]

19:33.830 --> 19:35.080
[ Thunder rumbles ]

19:40.540 --> 19:43.330
Levi: Natasha Deon, 45,
hospital day 62.

19:43.330 --> 19:44.960
Neuro unchanged,

19:44.960 --> 19:47.170
cardio -- she was
tachycardic overnight.

19:47.170 --> 19:50.250
Pulmonary -- she was placed back
on the ventilator two days ago.

19:50.250 --> 19:52.250
She's been awake
for four weeks.

19:52.250 --> 19:53.750
Why is she
back on the ventilator?

19:53.750 --> 19:55.670
She has pneumonia,
so she's on antibiotics,

19:55.670 --> 19:58.540
but her lungs have taken
a pretty big hit.

19:58.540 --> 20:02.540
GI -- Her tube feeds
were held for the O.R. today,

20:02.540 --> 20:04.500
but the CT
from overnight --

20:04.500 --> 20:07.790
My ostomy.
It's been hurting.

20:07.790 --> 20:09.500
Am I --
are you still gonna --

20:09.500 --> 20:12.380
We won't be able
to reverse your ostomy today.

20:12.380 --> 20:14.250
What? Why?

20:14.250 --> 20:15.750
The CT
that we got back,

20:15.750 --> 20:18.380
it showed fluid collections
in your abdomen,

20:18.380 --> 20:19.960
which may be
the source of your symptoms.

20:19.960 --> 20:22.460
What does that mean?
It means that we will
do surgery today,

20:22.460 --> 20:25.000
but it will be to clean out
the fluid collections.

20:25.000 --> 20:27.000
So you're gonna
open her back up?

20:27.000 --> 20:29.420
The wounds she's been working
to heal for the last few weeks?

20:29.420 --> 20:31.170
Unfortunately, yes.

20:32.750 --> 20:35.620
GU -- She is
on intermittent dialysis,

20:35.620 --> 20:38.080
and she is going to have
another session today.

20:38.080 --> 20:40.620
Heme -- she is
on DVT prophylaxis.

20:40.620 --> 20:43.080
♪♪

20:47.170 --> 20:48.500
[ Chuckles ]
Don't judge me.

20:48.500 --> 20:50.000
I saw a bed.
I laid down on it.

20:50.000 --> 20:51.500
My feet are
very angry with me.

20:51.500 --> 20:53.620
Ah.
I know what you need.

20:53.620 --> 20:56.000
And I know
just who to give it to you.

20:57.210 --> 20:59.580
Mimi at Pink Bunny.

20:59.580 --> 21:01.380
Best mani-pedi
in Seattle.

21:01.380 --> 21:03.330
[ Laughs ]
Why does it make perfect sense

21:03.330 --> 21:05.000
that you have
a favorite nail salon?

21:05.000 --> 21:06.290
Well, you don't want
to dig around somebody's brain

21:06.290 --> 21:07.540
with sloppy cuticles.

21:07.540 --> 21:10.170
You ever want to experience
pure bliss for $29 --

21:10.170 --> 21:12.000
Mnh! --
you let me know.

21:12.000 --> 21:13.790
[ Chuckles ]
[ Door opens ]

21:19.080 --> 21:21.290
Meredith:
Okay, cut the knot.

21:21.290 --> 21:24.000
[ Monitor beeping,
ventilator hissing ]

21:24.000 --> 21:25.830
Nicely done.
You can do the next tie.

21:27.750 --> 21:29.290
You seem different.

21:29.290 --> 21:30.580
I got contacts.

21:30.580 --> 21:32.170
No, it's --
it's not that.

21:32.170 --> 21:34.380
It's -- It's just
you're less...

21:34.380 --> 21:36.120
Glasses.

21:36.120 --> 21:37.460
-Yeah.
-Hmm.

21:37.460 --> 21:38.830
Yeah, and --
and the other day,

21:38.830 --> 21:41.120
when I asked you to change
Natasha's central line,

21:41.120 --> 21:43.420
you didn't mess it up
at all.

21:43.420 --> 21:46.830
Kind of a backhanded compliment,
but thank you?

21:50.210 --> 21:52.710
I met someone.
Mm.

21:52.710 --> 21:55.290
And he's hot,
and he's confident,

21:55.290 --> 21:56.460
and he likes me.

21:59.620 --> 22:01.750
And I'm gay.

22:01.750 --> 22:03.080
And he's gay.

22:03.080 --> 22:06.540
And we're...gay
together.

22:06.540 --> 22:09.920
And it's the most me I've
ever felt in my whole life.

22:09.920 --> 22:12.580
Well, I'm happy for you,
Schmitt.

22:12.580 --> 22:14.210
Thank you.

22:14.210 --> 22:16.120
DeLuca: Yeah,
I think it's beautiful.

22:16.120 --> 22:17.290
After all,
what's life for

22:17.290 --> 22:19.420
if not to share it
with somebody, right?

22:19.420 --> 22:21.710
Does that mean
life is not worth living alone?

22:21.710 --> 22:23.250
I think if you meet someone
who lights you up,

22:23.250 --> 22:24.750
you should
fight for them.

22:24.750 --> 22:26.380
Suction.

22:26.380 --> 22:28.710
[ Suction ]

22:28.710 --> 22:30.500
This fluid looks cloudy.

22:32.210 --> 22:33.880
Oh, no.

22:33.880 --> 22:35.580
She's got dead bowel.

22:35.580 --> 22:36.580
Jo: Did we know that?

22:36.580 --> 22:40.120
No, damn it.
G.I.A. stapler.

22:40.120 --> 22:42.500
Oh, God.
That's really bad, right?

22:42.500 --> 22:48.750
♪♪

22:48.750 --> 22:50.330
Last time I was here,
she was talking about

22:50.330 --> 22:52.620
someone named "Linus"
a lot.

22:52.620 --> 22:55.080
Is that a -- like, a boy?
Does she have a boyfriend?

22:55.080 --> 22:58.580
[ Door opens ]
She didn't call him that,
but I think so.

22:58.580 --> 23:00.960
Hey.
Hi!

23:08.500 --> 23:09.420
Was that him?

23:09.420 --> 23:10.620
Who?

23:10.620 --> 23:12.210
"Linus"?

23:12.210 --> 23:13.750
Uh, yeah, I guess.

23:13.750 --> 23:15.080
You guess?

23:17.380 --> 23:19.540
I'm doing
the stupid steps.

23:19.540 --> 23:24.120
Um, and I'm on the one
where you apologize for stuff

23:24.120 --> 23:25.250
and tell the truth.

23:25.250 --> 23:27.790
So, I have something
to tell you guys.

23:28.920 --> 23:30.670
Go ahead.
Okay.

23:30.670 --> 23:33.330
I've been lying to you guys
since I met you.

23:33.330 --> 23:34.960
My name's not Betty,

23:34.960 --> 23:37.960
and my parents
don't even know I'm here.

23:37.960 --> 23:39.500
But we've been
calling them.

23:39.500 --> 23:43.000
No, you've been talking
to my friend Jerry.

23:43.000 --> 23:45.460
Um, what's
your real name?

23:45.460 --> 23:47.750
Britney.

23:47.750 --> 23:48.960
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm sorry.

23:48.960 --> 23:50.380
[ Clears throat ]

23:50.380 --> 23:51.790
I know I should've told you,
but I was scared

23:51.790 --> 23:53.380
if they found out
about Leo.

23:53.380 --> 23:55.040
Whoa. Hold on.
They don't know about Leo?

23:55.040 --> 23:57.000
I ran away
when I got pregnant,

23:57.000 --> 23:59.710
and they've probably been
looking for me ever since.

23:59.710 --> 24:02.500
Okay. Um, well,
we have to call them now.

24:02.500 --> 24:04.250
No. No, no, no.
You can't.

24:04.250 --> 24:06.460
You can't.

24:06.460 --> 24:08.830
I'm not ready.

24:08.830 --> 24:11.040
And I'm scared
if they know about Leo,

24:11.040 --> 24:13.000
they're gonna take him.

24:13.000 --> 24:17.580
♪♪

24:17.580 --> 24:21.420
Natasha Deon, 45,
hospital day 73.

24:21.420 --> 24:23.620
Neuro --
I don't understand
what's happening.

24:23.620 --> 24:25.460
It feels like
every step forward she makes,

24:25.460 --> 24:27.080
she takes
two steps back.

24:27.080 --> 24:28.790
It's February 2nd.

24:28.790 --> 24:30.460
Groundhog Day.

24:30.460 --> 24:32.170
That's me.

24:32.170 --> 24:34.920
I feel like
I keep living the same day...

24:34.920 --> 24:36.380
[ Gulps ]

24:36.380 --> 24:38.620
...over and over.

24:38.620 --> 24:40.420
Okay, Bill Murray.

24:40.420 --> 24:43.790
Let the doctors tell us
what's going on.

24:43.790 --> 24:46.040
The reason we think she had
the dead bowel is that she's --

24:46.040 --> 24:48.250
[ Alarm blaring ]
Natasha?

24:48.250 --> 24:50.250
Okay, she's coding!
I'm gonna start compressions!

24:50.250 --> 24:51.750
Crack open the crash cart
and let's push

24:51.750 --> 24:53.120
one of atropine
and one of epi.

24:53.120 --> 24:54.920
Natasha!
Schmitt,
get him out of here.

24:54.920 --> 24:56.750
Natasha, please!
I need you!

24:56.750 --> 24:58.880
She probably
threw a PE --

24:58.880 --> 25:01.790
let's get an echo in here
and start a heparin drip.

25:01.790 --> 25:03.460
[ Blaring continues ]

25:03.460 --> 25:05.290
♪♪

25:10.540 --> 25:13.040
Natasha Deon, 45,
hospital day 84.

25:13.040 --> 25:14.170
Overnight,
she continued...

25:14.170 --> 25:18.250
Just tell me.
Please.

25:18.250 --> 25:21.460
Well, when she had her pulmonary
embolism 11 days ago,

25:21.460 --> 25:24.670
it -- it -- it weakened
her heart and her lungs.

25:24.670 --> 25:26.880
And since then, her kidneys
have worsened, as well.

25:26.880 --> 25:28.040
I'm sorry.
Why?

25:28.040 --> 25:30.000
Why?

25:30.000 --> 25:32.420
I just -- I --
Garrett, I --

25:32.420 --> 25:34.420
[ Voice breaking ]
Why is this happening to us?

25:34.420 --> 25:36.000
I don't have
an answer for that --

25:36.000 --> 25:38.290
Why is this happening
to us?

25:38.290 --> 25:40.710
She was getting better.

25:40.710 --> 25:43.170
After all
we went through.

25:43.170 --> 25:44.540
[ Hyperventilating ]

25:44.540 --> 25:46.080
Natasha...

25:46.080 --> 25:47.210
[ Groans ]

25:47.210 --> 25:48.330
Garrett?
Garrett.

25:48.330 --> 25:50.250
Hey, hey, hey.
Garrett.

25:50.250 --> 25:52.750
If she dies, I die.
If she dies, I die.

25:52.750 --> 25:54.620
Okay.
If she dies, I die.

25:54.620 --> 25:56.330
Garrett. Listen to me.
Look at me, please.

25:56.330 --> 25:57.420
Look at me.
Look at me. I'm here.

25:57.420 --> 25:59.620
Look at me, please.
Listen to me.

25:59.620 --> 26:01.040
You won't die.

26:01.040 --> 26:03.420
I know it feels like that
right now, but trust me.

26:03.420 --> 26:05.500
You won't die.

26:05.500 --> 26:07.620
You have to fight
for her.

26:07.620 --> 26:09.920
She's in there
fighting for you.

26:09.920 --> 26:11.290
You don't get to give up.

26:13.170 --> 26:16.620
So part of that fight is
you're gonna go take a walk,

26:16.620 --> 26:20.580
you're gonna take a shower,
and you're gonna get a meal.

26:20.580 --> 26:24.540
We will be here,
fighting to keep her alive.

26:24.540 --> 26:30.170
And you are gonna go fight
to keep yourself alive.

26:30.170 --> 26:32.080
Okay?

26:32.080 --> 26:33.580
Come on.

26:33.580 --> 26:37.460
♪♪

26:37.460 --> 26:40.540
♪ They don't love you
like I love you ♪

26:40.540 --> 26:42.420
♪ Wait ♪

26:42.420 --> 26:45.500
♪ They don't love you
like I love you ♪

26:45.500 --> 26:47.330
♪ Wait ♪

26:47.330 --> 26:50.380
♪ They don't love you
like I love you ♪

26:50.380 --> 26:54.330
♪ Maps ♪

26:54.330 --> 26:56.080
[ Grunts ]
Oh!

26:56.080 --> 26:58.120
[ Sobbing ]

27:00.290 --> 27:02.540
Oh, Catherine.

27:02.540 --> 27:04.000
Oh, honey.

27:05.750 --> 27:08.290
I can't do it!

27:08.290 --> 27:11.170
I can't.

27:11.170 --> 27:12.420
No!

27:12.420 --> 27:14.000
[ Sobs ]

27:14.000 --> 27:16.040
I can't...

27:16.040 --> 27:17.540
[ Leo fussing ]

27:17.540 --> 27:19.540
So, do you think Britney's
spelled with two "T"s or one?

27:19.540 --> 27:20.580
Or maybe they spell it
different,

27:20.580 --> 27:21.920
like with a "Y"
instead of "I", maybe?

27:21.920 --> 27:23.580
Owen,
you have to stop.

27:23.580 --> 27:25.040
We've been having this
conversation for two weeks.

27:25.040 --> 27:26.420
We just need
to find them.

27:26.420 --> 27:28.830
We need to tell them
where their daughter is.

27:28.830 --> 27:30.500
And have you thought about
what you're gonna say to them

27:30.500 --> 27:31.580
if you find them?

27:31.580 --> 27:33.540
"Hi,
we're two strangers.

27:33.540 --> 27:35.210
We took in
your daughter

27:35.210 --> 27:36.920
without going through
the foster system,

27:36.920 --> 27:39.330
and, oh, yeah,
we have her son,

27:39.330 --> 27:41.170
who you don't even
know exists.

27:41.170 --> 27:42.580
Congrats,
Grandma and Grandpa!"

27:42.580 --> 27:43.960
[ Scoffs ]

27:43.960 --> 27:46.540
We at least need to tell
the social worker.

27:46.540 --> 27:50.040
Owen, she -- she needs
to make that call herself.

27:50.040 --> 27:51.420
She's not ready.

27:51.420 --> 27:52.500
We can't push her.

27:52.500 --> 27:53.960
Why is she
running our lives?

27:53.960 --> 27:56.830
She's been lying to us, DCHS,
everyone for months,

27:56.830 --> 27:58.460
with no remorse.

27:58.460 --> 28:00.040
She had remorse.

28:00.040 --> 28:01.920
She's an addict.
She's figuring it out.

28:01.920 --> 28:04.080
This is all part
of the disease. Betty is --

28:04.080 --> 28:05.830
Her name
isn't even Betty!

28:05.830 --> 28:08.790
Sorry, I know that, yes, yes,
addiction is a disease,

28:08.790 --> 28:11.830
but since when does its symptoms
include lying

28:11.830 --> 28:14.250
and stealing from people
who are trying to help you?

28:14.250 --> 28:16.420
It just all feels
like an excuse

28:16.420 --> 28:18.920
for justifying
piss poor life choices.

28:18.920 --> 28:20.420
[ Keyboard clacking ]

28:20.420 --> 28:22.750
[ Sighs ]

28:26.080 --> 28:27.620
Wait,
where are you going?

28:27.620 --> 28:28.790
To Meredith's.

28:28.790 --> 28:30.960
Why?
I don't know.

28:30.960 --> 28:33.250
Piss poor life choices?

28:33.250 --> 28:35.000
Wait, wait, Amelia.

28:35.000 --> 28:37.040
I'm sorry.
That was way out of line.

28:37.040 --> 28:38.880
You don't even
see the line.

28:38.880 --> 28:40.500
[ Sighs ]

28:40.500 --> 28:42.750
I don't know who I'm gonna be
if they take Leo away.

28:42.750 --> 28:44.420
He's my son.

28:44.420 --> 28:45.540
[ Sighs ]

28:45.540 --> 28:48.790
If they're gonna
take him...

28:48.790 --> 28:51.040
I need to know
sooner than later.

28:54.250 --> 28:55.540
[ Leo coos ]

28:55.540 --> 28:59.170
♪♪

28:59.170 --> 29:01.540
Hey. I have a pitch
for tonight.

29:01.540 --> 29:03.380
You. Me.

29:03.380 --> 29:07.420
Movies. Pizza. Popcorn.
Candy. Sex.

29:07.420 --> 29:08.210
Repeat.

29:09.920 --> 29:11.330
You know
it's Valentine's Day, right?

29:11.330 --> 29:12.710
You hate Valentine's Day.

29:12.710 --> 29:14.580
I know.
I'm trying new things.

29:14.580 --> 29:16.540
Really?

29:19.330 --> 29:21.380
[ Sniffles ]

29:21.380 --> 29:22.960
I know you're hurting.

29:24.960 --> 29:27.380
I, um -- I don't...

29:27.380 --> 29:31.620
I don't know
how to make it better.

29:31.620 --> 29:33.880
Yeah, neither do I.

29:33.880 --> 29:37.040
I just -- I'm trying to do
normal stuff, you know?

29:37.040 --> 29:41.250
I just...feel so...

29:41.250 --> 29:43.960
[ Sighs ]

29:45.540 --> 29:47.500
On the worst day
of my mother's illness,

29:47.500 --> 29:50.460
I wanted to take her IV
and plunge it into my own arm.

29:52.540 --> 29:53.920
I wanted out.

29:53.920 --> 29:57.500
Not just of that day
or that moment.

29:57.500 --> 30:01.670
I wanted
out of this life.

30:01.670 --> 30:05.960
It was a fleeting thought,
but it came, and...

30:05.960 --> 30:08.710
you know, that's how bad
the pain was.

30:08.710 --> 30:10.170
That's how bad
the fear was.

30:13.880 --> 30:15.920
So what'd you do?

30:15.920 --> 30:17.920
I shook. I shook.

30:17.920 --> 30:19.330
[ Laughs ]

30:19.330 --> 30:21.580
My muscles shook in ways
that I did not know

30:21.580 --> 30:23.120
they could move.

30:23.120 --> 30:25.710
And then I, um...

30:25.710 --> 30:27.380
my eye
started twitching.

30:27.380 --> 30:30.420
Yeah. Yeah, my eye's been
twitching on and off all day.

30:30.420 --> 30:32.040
Mm.
And I've got, like,

30:32.040 --> 30:34.120
this shortness-of-breath thing
happening,

30:34.120 --> 30:36.120
where I can't
hold a deep breath.

30:36.120 --> 30:38.080
All day, every day.

30:40.170 --> 30:43.420
[ Dog barks in distance ]

30:43.420 --> 30:45.040
[ Smooches ]

30:47.580 --> 30:49.620
Hey, can I ask you
a question?
Yeah.

30:49.620 --> 30:51.960
How can you stand there and tell
Garrett to fight for love

30:51.960 --> 30:53.880
when you're the one
running away from it?

30:56.120 --> 30:59.040
I have three kids
and a big job.

31:00.830 --> 31:02.290
[ Telephone rings ]

31:04.500 --> 31:05.580
What?

31:05.580 --> 31:06.960
Nothing, just...
you know,

31:06.960 --> 31:09.250
I used to think you were
so beyond me, but you're not.

31:09.250 --> 31:11.500
You're like a kid
playing hide and seek,

31:11.500 --> 31:13.170
hiding behind
a million excuses.

31:13.170 --> 31:14.670
Happy Valentine's Day.

31:14.670 --> 31:16.000
Hi.

31:16.000 --> 31:18.750
Do you want to go
to dinner tonight?

31:18.750 --> 31:22.790
Are you...asking me out...
on Valentine's Day?

31:22.790 --> 31:24.210
I guess I am.

31:24.210 --> 31:25.670
Uh...
[ Chuckles ]

31:25.670 --> 31:27.330
Well, I'm, uh --

31:27.330 --> 31:30.080
I'm not one to usually
bang my head against a wall.

31:30.080 --> 31:31.250
Is that a no?
No, no.

31:31.250 --> 31:32.750
I'm banging my head.

31:32.750 --> 31:34.380
It's my new thing,
I guess.

31:34.380 --> 31:35.500
Um...

31:35.500 --> 31:38.000
I'll see you...
tonight?

31:38.000 --> 31:39.290
Okay.

31:39.290 --> 31:42.540
♪♪

31:42.540 --> 31:44.920
[ Hammering ]

31:51.420 --> 31:54.040
[ Engine shuts off,
car door opens, closes ]

31:54.040 --> 31:55.880
Ben,
you fixing the fence?

31:55.880 --> 31:57.330
You weren't
supposed to see me.

31:57.330 --> 31:58.420
Ah, Ben.

31:58.420 --> 32:00.040
N-No, Miranda,
Miranda, stop.

32:00.040 --> 32:02.830
Okay, it's my turn
to say things now.

32:02.830 --> 32:05.380
You said you wanted me
to be happy,

32:05.380 --> 32:07.080
to follow my bliss,

32:07.080 --> 32:09.500
and I did,
just like you told me to.

32:09.500 --> 32:11.460
And then you turned around
and left me over it.

32:11.460 --> 32:13.040
Now, I may be the one
sleeping somewhere else,

32:13.040 --> 32:15.330
but you left me.

32:15.330 --> 32:16.670
I know.

32:16.670 --> 32:18.170
I'm sorry.

32:18.170 --> 32:20.960
No, you can't leave me
like that again.

32:20.960 --> 32:22.460
Not ever. All right?

32:22.460 --> 32:25.040
You can take all the --
the job sabbaticals you want

32:25.040 --> 32:26.880
and -- and change your career
a dozen times,

32:26.880 --> 32:28.790
and I will be with you
every step of the way.

32:28.790 --> 32:32.540
But either we are in this
together or we aren't.

32:32.540 --> 32:34.210
And I never planned
a version where we weren't.

32:34.210 --> 32:35.290
I know --

32:35.290 --> 32:36.790
No, don't say
"I know."

32:36.790 --> 32:38.120
Listen to me.

32:39.580 --> 32:41.330
I should've known
something wasn't right with you.

32:41.330 --> 32:43.750
I-I should've
helped you get help.

32:43.750 --> 32:45.170
I-I should've --
I've seen it before.

32:45.170 --> 32:47.080
I should've
recognized it.

32:49.830 --> 32:51.920
When you had a heart attack,
I promised you

32:51.920 --> 32:54.540
I would build you
a treehouse,

32:54.540 --> 32:56.670
a place for you to go
when you would worry,

32:56.670 --> 32:58.960
when you felt overwhelmed,
when you needed to be alone,

32:58.960 --> 33:01.460
but I never followed through
on that.

33:03.210 --> 33:06.460
For that, I'm sorry.

33:06.460 --> 33:12.210
♪♪

33:12.210 --> 33:14.580
You're building me
a treehouse?

33:14.580 --> 33:17.750
Now, Miranda, I-I need to know
that this is not something

33:17.750 --> 33:20.540
that you can call "time out" on
ever again.

33:20.540 --> 33:21.830
Never.

33:21.830 --> 33:24.170
No, I-I promise you.

33:24.170 --> 33:26.250
Well, then, yeah,
I-I'm building you a treehouse.

33:26.250 --> 33:29.000
It's, uh -- It's not
finished yet, but, uh...

33:29.000 --> 33:30.790
I just figure, you know,
once I move back in,

33:30.790 --> 33:32.710
I can do a little bit of work
on it every morning.

33:32.710 --> 33:33.880
[ Laughs ]

33:33.880 --> 33:36.040
Oh!

33:36.040 --> 33:37.920
Oh!

33:37.920 --> 33:40.920
♪♪

33:40.920 --> 33:43.710
[ Monitor beeping,
ventilator hissing ]

33:43.710 --> 33:45.380
Dr. Schmitt said
you had something

33:45.380 --> 33:47.080
you want to discuss
with us?

33:51.460 --> 33:56.380
We've been in this hospital now
for over three months.

33:56.380 --> 33:58.540
Since then,
Natasha's only gotten worse.

33:58.540 --> 34:01.120
And I know you're
the best doctors we could get

34:01.120 --> 34:03.120
because I tried
to find better ones,

34:03.120 --> 34:05.920
but I couldn't.

34:05.920 --> 34:07.580
No offense.

34:13.920 --> 34:15.710
[ Weakly ]
Take me off the vent.

34:19.420 --> 34:21.710
I can't eat.

34:21.710 --> 34:24.170
I can't breathe.

34:26.000 --> 34:27.540
I'm dying.

34:30.670 --> 34:31.920
There are
other options.

34:31.920 --> 34:33.580
There's
home ventilator care.

34:33.580 --> 34:35.290
There's
long-term acute care.

34:35.290 --> 34:37.540
There's skilled
nursing facilities.

34:37.540 --> 34:38.790
They know.

34:38.790 --> 34:42.250
They've been consulting
palliative care doctors.

34:42.250 --> 34:45.790
You all have done
everything you can

34:45.790 --> 34:49.000
to give me
as much time as possible.

34:51.960 --> 34:54.380
We may not have gotten

34:54.380 --> 34:56.620
that wedding
under the stars, but...

34:56.620 --> 34:59.750
[ Sobs ]

34:59.750 --> 35:04.000
...you gave us
the rest of our lives together.

35:08.920 --> 35:11.920
[ Sniffling ]

35:11.920 --> 35:14.710
Take me off.

35:14.710 --> 35:16.080
Please.

35:17.830 --> 35:19.120
Please.

35:24.540 --> 35:26.170
We need you
to give verbal consent

35:26.170 --> 35:27.460
as her power of attorney.

35:27.460 --> 35:29.290
[ Monitor beeping,
ventilator hissing ]

35:29.290 --> 35:30.880
[ Voice breaking ]
I consent.

35:33.290 --> 35:35.710
So, once I shut
the machine off,

35:35.710 --> 35:38.210
I don't know
how much time you'll have,

35:38.210 --> 35:40.380
so we will give you meds
to keep you comfortable.

35:42.170 --> 35:43.540
Are you ready?

35:45.500 --> 35:47.210
Yeah.

35:47.210 --> 35:48.040
Okay.

35:49.580 --> 35:51.920
[ Switch clicks ]

35:51.920 --> 35:54.500
[ Machine powers down ]

35:54.500 --> 35:56.670
[ Coughing ]

36:00.960 --> 36:03.120
[ Air hisses ]

36:06.710 --> 36:08.460
[ Sniffling ]

36:08.460 --> 36:11.000
[ Crying ]

36:11.000 --> 36:17.210
♪♪

36:17.210 --> 36:20.920
♪♪

36:20.920 --> 36:22.460
Alex has an idea.

36:22.460 --> 36:24.040
[ Garrett sniffles ]

36:24.040 --> 36:33.500
♪♪

36:33.500 --> 36:35.880
Since when
do we do Valentine's?

36:35.880 --> 36:38.040
Since I've been an ass
and needed an excuse
to make it up to you.

36:38.040 --> 36:39.540
Ah, that's my cue.

36:39.540 --> 36:41.620
I have a date,
for which I cannot be late.

36:41.620 --> 36:42.710
Teddy: Hey.

36:45.330 --> 36:46.580
Hi.

36:50.040 --> 36:51.460
Happy Valentine's Day.

36:51.460 --> 36:52.790
Uh, yeah.
Yeah.

36:52.790 --> 36:54.120
[ Chuckles ]
Hey.

36:57.290 --> 36:59.000
Hey, are you guys free
to come to the ICU?

36:59.000 --> 36:59.920
What's up?
Just -- Just come.

36:59.920 --> 37:02.580
Bring your phones.

37:02.580 --> 37:12.170
♪♪

37:12.170 --> 37:17.120
♪ When the night has come ♪

37:19.250 --> 37:21.170
Your doctors
wanted to make sure

37:21.170 --> 37:23.670
we got our wedding
under the stars.

37:23.670 --> 37:32.580
♪ And the moon
is the only light we see ♪

37:32.580 --> 37:34.540
Meredith: Garrett asked me
to read the vows

37:34.540 --> 37:37.380
that you wrote
before the accident.

37:37.380 --> 37:39.920
♪ ...be afraid ♪

37:39.920 --> 37:45.710
♪ No, I won't be afraid ♪

37:45.710 --> 37:46.830
♪ Just as long... ♪

37:46.830 --> 37:50.250
"Garrett, the moment I met you,

37:50.250 --> 37:53.290
I knew I would spend
the rest of my life with you.

37:53.290 --> 37:54.960
Before you, I never met anyone

37:54.960 --> 37:57.670
I could be in the same room
with longer than a few hours."

37:57.670 --> 37:58.670
[ Laughter ]

37:58.670 --> 38:01.620
♪ Darlin', stand by me ♪

38:01.620 --> 38:05.670
"I waited my whole life
to meet you.

38:05.670 --> 38:09.080
I gave up thinking
I ever would."

38:09.080 --> 38:10.670
♪ Oh, stand ♪

38:10.670 --> 38:12.250
"But here we are.

38:12.250 --> 38:13.790
Better late than never, right?"

38:13.790 --> 38:15.920
♪ Stand by me ♪

38:15.920 --> 38:18.710
"Now that I found you,
it all makes sense.

38:18.710 --> 38:23.330
Everything that was once hard
feels easy

38:23.330 --> 38:26.290
now that you are in my life.

38:26.290 --> 38:30.290
And everything that was
once easy is now sublime."

38:30.290 --> 38:36.710
♪♪

38:36.710 --> 38:37.880
I'm sorry.

38:37.880 --> 38:39.290
I love you.

38:39.290 --> 38:42.580
I'm sorry
I've been so impossible.

38:42.580 --> 38:45.620
No, no, you do not get to
apologize, sweetheart.

38:45.620 --> 38:49.710
I can't begin to understand
what you're going through.

38:49.710 --> 38:52.080
But I promise

38:52.080 --> 38:54.710
I'll be at your side
while you do it.

38:54.710 --> 38:56.580
Mm.

38:56.580 --> 39:00.000
♪♪

39:00.000 --> 39:01.790
And...

39:01.790 --> 39:05.580
Catherine Fox.

39:05.580 --> 39:07.080
Easy.

39:07.080 --> 39:09.170
♪ I won't cry ♪

39:09.170 --> 39:12.120
You couldn't be average
if you tried.

39:12.120 --> 39:17.710
♪ No, I won't shed a tear ♪

39:17.710 --> 39:18.710
♪ Just as long... ♪

39:18.710 --> 39:20.120
Mnh.

39:20.120 --> 39:21.670
W-What's the matter?

39:21.670 --> 39:23.920
Get me
to that bedroom now.

39:23.920 --> 39:25.710
♪ Stand by me ♪

39:25.710 --> 39:27.120
She's back, baby.

39:27.120 --> 39:28.920
[ Both laugh ]

39:28.920 --> 39:33.380
♪ Darlin', stand by me ♪

39:33.380 --> 39:35.620
Chaplain: Do you, Garrett,
take this woman to be your wife?

39:35.620 --> 39:37.920
I do.

39:37.920 --> 39:40.790
And do you, Natasha, take
this man to be your husband?

39:40.790 --> 39:42.960
[ Grunts softly ]

39:45.040 --> 39:47.540
♪ Stand by me ♪

39:47.540 --> 39:49.500
By the power vested in me,

39:49.500 --> 39:53.080
I now pronounce you
husband and wife.

39:53.080 --> 39:54.460
[ Chuckles ]

39:58.580 --> 40:00.170
♪ Stand by me ♪

40:00.170 --> 40:02.580
Don't -- Don't...

40:02.580 --> 40:03.710
I know.

40:03.710 --> 40:06.330
♪ Stand by, oh ♪

40:06.330 --> 40:08.040
Thank you.

40:08.040 --> 40:09.620
[ Voice breaking ]
Thank you for marrying me.

40:09.620 --> 40:11.460
♪ Stand by me ♪

40:15.620 --> 40:18.170
♪ Stand by me ♪

40:20.790 --> 40:23.040
♪ Stand by me ♪

40:26.120 --> 40:28.670
♪ Stand by me ♪

40:28.670 --> 40:38.620
♪♪

40:38.620 --> 40:45.170
♪♪

40:45.170 --> 40:47.040
Meredith:
There's never enough time.

40:49.330 --> 40:50.920
Come with me.

40:50.920 --> 40:54.290
Work, kids, life...

40:54.290 --> 40:56.330
death.

40:56.330 --> 40:58.380
Something always
cuts our time short.

40:58.380 --> 40:59.380
[ Door closes ]

40:59.380 --> 41:01.080
I'm supposed to be
on a date.

41:01.080 --> 41:03.540
You already are.

41:03.540 --> 41:09.500
♪♪

41:09.500 --> 41:15.620
♪♪

41:15.620 --> 41:17.040
A toast.

41:17.040 --> 41:18.380
To Garrett
and Natasha.

41:19.920 --> 41:21.540
[ Sighs ]

41:21.540 --> 41:24.460
To Garrett
and Natasha.

41:24.460 --> 41:29.710
So our best bet is to make
the most of the time we have.

41:29.710 --> 41:32.120
[ Moaning ]
♪ I want to give myself
permission ♪

41:32.120 --> 41:33.880
♪ I don't wanna hold it in ♪

41:33.880 --> 41:36.620
Oh, oh, oh.
This is better than sex.

41:36.620 --> 41:38.960
Every pregnant woman I bring
here says the same thing.

41:38.960 --> 41:40.790
[ Laughing ] What?

41:40.790 --> 41:43.290
You are just so...

41:43.290 --> 41:45.710
I know. I am so.

41:45.710 --> 41:46.830
♪ I vow, I vow ♪

41:46.830 --> 41:48.120
But not as so as you.

41:49.670 --> 41:52.710
Ah, dinner is here.

41:52.710 --> 41:54.250
Thank you.
Mmm.

41:54.250 --> 41:56.330
Do you like?
Yeah, I like.

41:56.330 --> 41:58.830
Yeah?
